WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.179 --> 00:00:11.322
Where do you think you're going?

2
00:00:11.346 --> 00:00:12.556
Reacher!

3
00:00:12.639 --> 00:00:13.932
Reacher. get back here!

4
00:00:14.016 --> 00:00:16.560
Maybe give him some space.

5
00:00:16.643 --> 00:00:19.813
I don't need 250 pounds
of frontier justice

6
00:00:19.897 --> 00:00:21.064
tearing up this town.

7
00:00:23.650 --> 00:00:25.461
Follow him. make sure
he doesn't ruin our case.

8
00:00:25.485 --> 00:00:26.612
Why me?

9
00:00:27.362 --> 00:00:29.242
Outside the morgue.
he actually listened to you.

10
00:00:30.866 --> 00:00:32.326
And what if he doesn't now?

11
00:00:32.409 --> 00:00:33.410
Shoot him.

12
00:01:08.654 --> 00:01:11.031
<i>We got a stranded vehicle</i>

13
00:01:11.114 --> 00:01:13.200
<i>around 80 on the eastbound side.</i>

14
00:01:22.209 --> 00:01:24.544
<i>247. About ten out.</i>

15
00:01:35.722 --> 00:01:37.307
Shit!

16
00:01:39.101 --> 00:01:41.270
The hell? I could have hit you.

17
00:01:41.353 --> 00:01:43.039
I don't need a babysitter
and I don't need you

18
00:01:43.063 --> 00:01:44.564
screwing up my investigation.

19
00:01:44.648 --> 00:01:48.360
Okay. first...
this is not your investigation.

20
00:01:48.443 --> 00:01:50.529
Second. babysitting some giant vagrant

21
00:01:50.612 --> 00:01:51.989
is hardly my dream assignment.

22
00:01:52.072 --> 00:01:54.175
I could be out there looking
for who killed your brother.

23
00:01:54.199 --> 00:01:56.660
So stand down and let me do my job.

24
00:01:56.743 --> 00:01:58.120
because I'm very good at it.

25
00:01:58.203 --> 00:02:00.484
If you were very good at it.
you wouldn't have been trying

26
00:02:00.539 --> 00:02:02.207
to follow a man on foot
in a police car.

27
00:02:04.209 --> 00:02:05.929
I figure your plan's to go
to Hubble's house

28
00:02:05.961 --> 00:02:07.355
and dig your thumb
into his eye until he tells you

29
00:02:07.379 --> 00:02:09.065
why he confessed to a murder
he didn't commit.

30
00:02:09.089 --> 00:02:10.650
- Something like that.
- Yeah. well. I'm gonna be there

31
00:02:10.674 --> 00:02:12.092
to make sure that doesn't happen.

32
00:02:12.175 --> 00:02:14.136
Now. I can either follow you
the whole way.

33
00:02:14.219 --> 00:02:16.459
or you can save the shoe leather
and get in the damn car.

34
00:02:26.231 --> 00:02:27.274
Fuck.

35
00:02:35.949 --> 00:02:38.201
For the record.
I'm not a vagrant. I'm a hobo.

36
00:02:41.455 --> 00:02:42.456
Whatever.

37
00:02:48.587 --> 00:02:51.423
Officer Conklin. uh.
Mr. Reacher. please come in.

38
00:02:55.052 --> 00:02:57.971
I'm so sorry.
Paul won't be back till late.

39
00:02:58.055 --> 00:03:01.391
But at least now I get a chance
to thank you. Mr. Reacher.

40
00:03:01.475 --> 00:03:03.268
- It's just Reacher.
- Well.

41
00:03:04.019 --> 00:03:05.437
Reacher.

42
00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:08.273
My husband told me that you looked out
for him in that awful prison.

43
00:03:09.941 --> 00:03:11.234
Please. have a seat.

44
00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:17.449
Do you. uh...
Do you know where Paul is?

45
00:03:18.742 --> 00:03:20.619
No. not specifically.

46
00:03:20.702 --> 00:03:22.996
He's dealing with that
embezzlement mess.

47
00:03:23.080 --> 00:03:24.706
Thank God he was cleared of all that.

48
00:03:24.790 --> 00:03:26.150
Can you imagine? Paul. a criminal?

49
00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:28.585
Man's never
so much as jaywalked.

50
00:03:28.668 --> 00:03:30.548
I assume that's why you're here.
The bank stuff?

51
00:03:31.338 --> 00:03:32.881
No.

52
00:03:32.964 --> 00:03:33.965
My brother was murdered.

53
00:03:34.591 --> 00:03:35.884
Dear God. I...

54
00:03:37.386 --> 00:03:39.429
I don't know what to say.

55
00:03:39.513 --> 00:03:41.264
That the man they found
by the highway?

56
00:03:41.348 --> 00:03:43.141
He was.

57
00:03:43.225 --> 00:03:45.185
And he had your husband's
telephone number on him.

58
00:03:46.561 --> 00:03:48.313
Well. that doesn't make
any sense. Why?

59
00:03:48.397 --> 00:03:49.832
Well. that's what
we're here to find out.

60
00:03:49.856 --> 00:03:52.275
Why my dead brother had your
live husband's number on him.

61
00:03:54.152 --> 00:03:55.153
Well. I have no idea.

62
00:03:55.237 --> 00:03:56.238
Momma?

63
00:03:58.323 --> 00:04:00.367
Is it 8:30 already?

64
00:04:00.450 --> 00:04:02.702
I'm sorry. but I've got to get
these two to bed.

65
00:04:02.786 --> 00:04:05.580
Girls. say hi
to Officer Conklin and Mr. Reacher.

66
00:04:05.664 --> 00:04:07.141
- Hello. Officer Conklin.
- Hello. Mr. Reacher.

67
00:04:07.165 --> 00:04:08.768
- Hello. Mr. Reacher.
- Hello. Officer Conklin.

68
00:04:08.792 --> 00:04:12.129
- Mmm-hmm.
- It's just... Reacher.

69
00:04:12.212 --> 00:04:15.090
Well. this is Lucy and Tally.

70
00:04:15.173 --> 00:04:17.217
- Have y'all brushed your teeth?
- Yes.

71
00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.140
All right. then get on.
I'll be up in a minute.

72
00:04:21.138 --> 00:04:22.514
Well. Tally's growing like a weed.

73
00:04:22.597 --> 00:04:24.391
Yeah. I know.

74
00:04:24.474 --> 00:04:25.851
She's the one with the glasses.

75
00:04:26.726 --> 00:04:29.813
Can you believe she's
a year younger than Lucy?

76
00:04:29.896 --> 00:04:31.231
May I use your restroom?

77
00:04:31.690 --> 00:04:34.370
Yeah. of course. Through the kitchen.
down the hall and to the left.

78
00:05:28.538 --> 00:05:30.290
...something like this happens.

79
00:05:34.252 --> 00:05:35.712
We've taken up enough of your time.

80
00:05:35.795 --> 00:05:37.005
Have a nice evening.

81
00:05:37.088 --> 00:05:38.131
Roscoe.

82
00:05:41.468 --> 00:05:43.887
Um...
Well. guess we're going.

83
00:05:44.679 --> 00:05:46.014
- Sorry about that.
- No.

84
00:05:46.097 --> 00:05:47.857
Have a good evening.
Thank you for your time.

85
00:05:47.933 --> 00:05:49.434
and. uh...

86
00:05:49.518 --> 00:05:50.936
- I'll see you.
- Yes. Good night.

87
00:05:58.527 --> 00:05:59.528
That was an exit.

88
00:05:59.653 --> 00:06:03.698
Two things. One. she said Tally
is the one in the glasses.

89
00:06:03.782 --> 00:06:05.301
Glasses is the main difference
between the girls.

90
00:06:05.325 --> 00:06:06.910
Everything else was
a matter of degree.

91
00:06:06.993 --> 00:06:09.454
taller. shorter.
but glasses was absolute.

92
00:06:09.538 --> 00:06:10.598
One wears them. one doesn't.

93
00:06:10.622 --> 00:06:12.249
And?

94
00:06:12.332 --> 00:06:13.852
Right before I was attacked in prison.

95
00:06:13.917 --> 00:06:15.418
a guy pointed at me and said. "Him."

96
00:06:15.502 --> 00:06:17.003
I'd taken a guy's glasses.

97
00:06:17.087 --> 00:06:20.382
- Why?
- 'Cause he wasn't a nice man.

98
00:06:20.465 --> 00:06:23.343
I still had them on
when these cons came at me.

99
00:06:23.426 --> 00:06:25.446
Their instructions were clearly
to find the new boys

100
00:06:25.470 --> 00:06:27.681
and take out the one in glasses.

101
00:06:27.764 --> 00:06:30.225
Hubble's had been smashed.
He was the target. not me.

102
00:06:30.308 --> 00:06:32.394
Hubble's on the run.
or they've already got him.

103
00:06:33.436 --> 00:06:34.896
Okay.

104
00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:36.273
You said there were two things.

105
00:06:37.148 --> 00:06:38.483
This is some kind of seed.

106
00:06:39.734 --> 00:06:41.614
Why would a banker have them
on his dress shoes?

107
00:06:41.861 --> 00:06:42.862
You went in his closet?

108
00:06:43.321 --> 00:06:44.573
No. Mud room.

109
00:06:46.157 --> 00:06:47.367
It's an agrimony burr.

110
00:06:47.450 --> 00:06:48.928
They grow on tall grass
all around here.

111
00:06:48.952 --> 00:06:50.721
We call them hitchhikers.
'cause they stick on you

112
00:06:50.745 --> 00:06:51.913
and they go for a ride.

113
00:06:54.249 --> 00:06:55.875
They grow where my brother was killed?

114
00:07:04.926 --> 00:07:06.219
This is cogongrass.

115
00:07:06.303 --> 00:07:08.763
Had it on my uncle's farm.
It doesn't produce burrs.

116
00:07:08.847 --> 00:07:10.473
Okay.

117
00:07:10.557 --> 00:07:13.935
Still some reason
they were on his laces.

118
00:07:14.019 --> 00:07:16.062
You don't pick up hitchhikers
in bank hallways.

119
00:07:23.111 --> 00:07:25.381
I told Finlay the shooter was
someone who knew firearms well.

120
00:07:25.405 --> 00:07:27.365
but it was more than that.

121
00:07:27.449 --> 00:07:28.593
Killer was a skilled marksman.

122
00:07:28.617 --> 00:07:30.035
What makes you think that?

123
00:07:30.118 --> 00:07:32.370
Second victim was
sprinting away in the dark.

124
00:07:32.454 --> 00:07:34.974
Gun had a silencer on it. which makes
even close-range work inaccurate.

125
00:07:34.998 --> 00:07:35.999
but he got a kill shot.

126
00:07:39.961 --> 00:07:41.254
Prints are Joe's.

127
00:07:41.338 --> 00:07:43.131
Size 13. See the divot?

128
00:07:43.214 --> 00:07:44.275
Heard someone coming up behind him.

129
00:07:44.299 --> 00:07:45.699
Tried to turn. Took two in the head

130
00:07:45.759 --> 00:07:47.239
before he could do anything about it.

131
00:07:51.765 --> 00:07:53.141
Shooter came through here.

132
00:07:54.643 --> 00:07:55.727
Waiting for Joe.

133
00:07:56.811 --> 00:07:58.104
Knew he was coming.

134
00:08:04.444 --> 00:08:07.155
Two days ago. moon would have
been about 26 degrees further west.

135
00:08:10.617 --> 00:08:12.077
This area would have been darker.

136
00:08:15.664 --> 00:08:16.790
This is where he hid.

137
00:08:24.297 --> 00:08:25.423
He enjoyed it.

138
00:08:28.134 --> 00:08:29.278
Sniper shot from the tree line

139
00:08:29.302 --> 00:08:30.822
would have done the job
with less risk.

140
00:08:32.972 --> 00:08:34.265
The shooter wanted to be close.

141
00:08:34.724 --> 00:08:36.017
Maybe it was personal.

142
00:08:36.101 --> 00:08:38.478
Someone takes your life.
it's always personal.

143
00:08:48.446 --> 00:08:49.447
Tell me about Joe.

144
00:08:51.366 --> 00:08:52.367
Were you guys tight?

145
00:08:58.540 --> 00:08:59.833
Did he have a family?

146
00:09:00.625 --> 00:09:02.919
What'd he do for a living?

147
00:09:03.002 --> 00:09:05.755
Small talk to see if I say
something to help your investigation?

148
00:09:07.298 --> 00:09:09.300
I'm being nice to a guy
who just lost his brother.

149
00:09:09.384 --> 00:09:10.861
But. you know.
now that you brought it up.

150
00:09:10.885 --> 00:09:12.363
you might as well answer my questions.

151
00:09:12.387 --> 00:09:14.305
In order. when we were kids.
no family.

152
00:09:14.389 --> 00:09:16.450
last time we spoke he was working
in Homeland Security.

153
00:09:16.474 --> 00:09:18.643
That's interesting.

154
00:09:18.727 --> 00:09:20.871
You think that this might
have been connected to his job?

155
00:09:20.895 --> 00:09:23.314
Homeland's a big umbrella.
terrorism. drugs.

156
00:09:23.398 --> 00:09:24.691
guns. border crimes.

157
00:09:24.774 --> 00:09:27.527
- What department was your brother in?
- Don't know.

158
00:09:29.070 --> 00:09:30.321
We hadn't spoken in a while.

159
00:09:31.614 --> 00:09:32.615
Why?

160
00:09:34.617 --> 00:09:35.744
Time passed.

161
00:09:37.245 --> 00:09:38.538
Where you going?

162
00:09:38.621 --> 00:09:39.789
To find a motel.

163
00:09:39.873 --> 00:09:41.040
I'll give you a ride.

164
00:09:41.916 --> 00:09:42.917
Don't want one.

165
00:10:07.317 --> 00:10:08.943
Hey. Mister.

166
00:10:09.027 --> 00:10:10.945
Why don't you come here?
We want to talk to you.

167
00:10:11.029 --> 00:10:13.323
- No. you don't.
- "No. you don't."

168
00:10:13.865 --> 00:10:15.241
Hey. come here.

169
00:10:15.325 --> 00:10:17.410
We just want to talk to you.

170
00:10:17.494 --> 00:10:20.205
Heard you got arrested for murder.

171
00:10:20.288 --> 00:10:22.624
What kind of bullshit
you bring into our town?

172
00:10:30.715 --> 00:10:32.526
There's two sixers' worth
of empties around your car.

173
00:10:32.550 --> 00:10:33.927
You've been waiting a while.

174
00:10:34.010 --> 00:10:35.738
And since this isn't the most
exciting spot in town.

175
00:10:35.762 --> 00:10:37.442
I got to assume you've been
waiting for me.

176
00:10:38.723 --> 00:10:41.351
Let me guess.
Rich guy in a fancy pickup

177
00:10:41.434 --> 00:10:43.812
put a fifty in each of your
pockets to take care of me?

178
00:10:44.938 --> 00:10:46.397
Hundred.

179
00:10:46.481 --> 00:10:49.108
Right. Well. this is
the wrong day to ask me

180
00:10:49.192 --> 00:10:50.360
to humor your bullshit.

181
00:10:50.443 --> 00:10:51.444
Hey!

182
00:10:53.279 --> 00:10:54.489
We're talking to you. man.

183
00:11:01.162 --> 00:11:02.831
Oh. Graham. you idiot.

184
00:11:02.914 --> 00:11:04.582
You're about to get your ass kicked.

185
00:11:04.666 --> 00:11:06.793
No.

186
00:11:06.876 --> 00:11:08.920
I'm just gonna break the hands
of three drunk kids.

187
00:11:09.003 --> 00:11:11.339
There's four of us here.

188
00:11:11.422 --> 00:11:13.508
One of you has got to drive
to the hospital.

189
00:11:13.591 --> 00:11:14.968
Ooh...

190
00:11:22.976 --> 00:11:25.019
I... I know where the hospital is.

191
00:11:32.443 --> 00:11:34.821
What the hell just
rolled into Margrave?

192
00:12:41.512 --> 00:12:42.805
Hey. buddy.

193
00:12:43.890 --> 00:12:45.016
You okay?

194
00:12:51.522 --> 00:12:53.733
- Good boy.
- Hey. Hey.

195
00:12:53.816 --> 00:12:55.818
- Can I help you?
- No.

196
00:12:55.902 --> 00:12:57.362
Just giving your dog some water.

197
00:12:58.488 --> 00:12:59.948
He must've knocked the bowl over.

198
00:13:00.031 --> 00:13:01.511
'cause I gave him water this morning.

199
00:13:02.241 --> 00:13:03.701
No. you didn't.

200
00:13:03.785 --> 00:13:05.203
Bowl was bone-dry.

201
00:13:05.787 --> 00:13:06.829
You calling me a liar?

202
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:11.751
Yes.

203
00:13:15.088 --> 00:13:17.048
Well. I suggest you leave my property.

204
00:13:21.135 --> 00:13:22.220
Good boy.

205
00:13:42.323 --> 00:13:43.700
What are you doing here?

206
00:13:43.783 --> 00:13:47.203
Wanted to check in. see if there's
any official progress on Joe's case

207
00:13:47.286 --> 00:13:49.122
before I head back out to Hubble's.

208
00:13:49.205 --> 00:13:51.499
I can't talk right now.
There's been another murder.

209
00:13:51.582 --> 00:13:52.750
Police Chief Morrison.

210
00:13:55.128 --> 00:13:56.879
For the record. I didn't do it.

211
00:13:56.963 --> 00:13:57.964
I know.

212
00:13:58.047 --> 00:13:59.274
Because you staked me out all night?

213
00:14:10.476 --> 00:14:12.645
Last night you wanted
to go everywhere with me.

214
00:14:29.203 --> 00:14:30.288
Captain.

215
00:14:30.371 --> 00:14:31.956
What did they do to the chief?

216
00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:33.458
Baker won't talk about it.

217
00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:36.419
Just keep the lookie-loos away.
all right?

218
00:14:41.007 --> 00:14:42.050
Yes. sir.

219
00:14:46.888 --> 00:14:47.972
What is he doing here?

220
00:14:48.056 --> 00:14:49.116
You told me
to keep an eye on him.

221
00:14:49.140 --> 00:14:50.180
I'm keeping an eye on him.

222
00:14:50.224 --> 00:14:52.060
Look. There he is.

223
00:14:53.478 --> 00:14:56.189
Crime scene's worse than
anything I ever saw in Boston.

224
00:14:56.272 --> 00:14:58.649
And I saw things in Boston.

225
00:14:58.733 --> 00:14:59.859
Was he nailed to a wall?

226
00:15:01.611 --> 00:15:02.904
How did you know that?

227
00:15:06.199 --> 00:15:07.200
Hey.

228
00:15:27.261 --> 00:15:28.906
These lacerations
appear to be shallow

229
00:15:28.930 --> 00:15:31.015
and were possibly done
with a serrated blade.

230
00:15:31.099 --> 00:15:33.101
which leads me to believe
that they were intended

231
00:15:33.184 --> 00:15:35.520
to inflict pain
rather than cause death.

232
00:15:35.603 --> 00:15:38.856
Preliminary examination
of Police Chief Edward Morrison.

233
00:15:38.940 --> 00:15:41.234
Subject has been nailed
to the wall contralaterally

234
00:15:41.317 --> 00:15:42.735
with six spikes.

235
00:15:42.819 --> 00:15:45.279
two of which were driven between
the ulna and the radius

236
00:15:45.363 --> 00:15:47.323
- near the wrist and...
- Jesus Christ.

237
00:15:47.740 --> 00:15:50.743
One laceration to the left cheek.

238
00:15:50.827 --> 00:15:51.828
Prints?

239
00:15:51.911 --> 00:15:54.705
I asked a question just like this one.

240
00:15:54.789 --> 00:15:56.029
how'd you know about the nails?

241
00:15:56.082 --> 00:15:58.459
Even in Margrave.
word doesn't travel that fast.

242
00:16:00.294 --> 00:16:03.381
They wore rubber overshoes
and gloves. Latex.

243
00:16:03.464 --> 00:16:05.049
Like whoever killed my brother.

244
00:16:05.424 --> 00:16:06.425
What makes you say that?

245
00:16:06.843 --> 00:16:08.594
Well. three people killed my brother.

246
00:16:08.678 --> 00:16:10.638
At least four to do that
to a guy Morrison's size.

247
00:16:10.680 --> 00:16:12.849
Holy shit. his fucking balls are gone!

248
00:16:13.516 --> 00:16:15.184
Keep it professional. Jasper.

249
00:16:15.768 --> 00:16:18.104
Cursing's the sign of a weak mind
and a weaker character.

250
00:16:18.187 --> 00:16:20.148
Sorry. I'm just not used to this.

251
00:16:20.231 --> 00:16:22.376
You don't see this kind of thing
every day.

252
00:16:22.400 --> 00:16:23.568
Pardon my French. but...

253
00:16:23.651 --> 00:16:25.528
Where the heck
are his testicles?

254
00:16:25.611 --> 00:16:26.779
In his stomach.

255
00:16:31.033 --> 00:16:32.473
You'll find them during the autopsy.

256
00:16:34.120 --> 00:16:35.955
Okay. Reacher. outside.

257
00:16:44.422 --> 00:16:45.590
No more games.

258
00:16:45.673 --> 00:16:46.966
How do you know what you know?

259
00:16:47.383 --> 00:16:49.319
The people Hubble worked for
said they'd nail him to a wall

260
00:16:49.343 --> 00:16:51.429
and cut his balls off
if he caused problems.

261
00:16:51.512 --> 00:16:53.931
You said Hubble
didn't tell you anything in jail.

262
00:16:54.015 --> 00:16:57.727
I lied. My brother didn't trust
Margrave cops enough to tell you

263
00:16:57.810 --> 00:16:59.621
he was tracking something
down here. Why should I?

264
00:16:59.645 --> 00:17:01.665
Ever think your brother
didn't reach out to the cops

265
00:17:01.689 --> 00:17:03.649
because he couldn't
reach out to the cops?

266
00:17:03.733 --> 00:17:04.793
Maybe he was dirty. Maybe...

267
00:17:04.817 --> 00:17:06.736
Think real hard before
you finish that sentence.

268
00:17:06.819 --> 00:17:09.259
It'll determine how well
your jaw works the rest of your life.

269
00:17:09.697 --> 00:17:10.823
Joe was clean.

270
00:17:10.907 --> 00:17:12.825
Unlike that modern art piece
hanging inside.

271
00:17:12.909 --> 00:17:15.369
So you're saying that
Morrison was working

272
00:17:15.453 --> 00:17:17.914
with the same killers
Hubble was mixed up with?

273
00:17:17.997 --> 00:17:20.625
That. or we just saw a big fat
coincidence nailed to the wall.

274
00:17:22.168 --> 00:17:24.449
What I want to know is who else
in Margrave PD's in on it.

275
00:17:25.171 --> 00:17:27.091
Stevenson seems suspicious.
and Baker wouldn't go

276
00:17:27.131 --> 00:17:29.008
into the bathroom with me
at the station house.

277
00:17:29.091 --> 00:17:30.468
A bathroom with a window in it.

278
00:17:30.927 --> 00:17:31.928
I was a murder suspect.

279
00:17:32.011 --> 00:17:33.471
Baker wasn't concerned

280
00:17:33.554 --> 00:17:34.972
'cause he knew you didn't do it.

281
00:17:35.056 --> 00:17:36.216
Which means he knows who did.

282
00:17:36.265 --> 00:17:38.601
Want to tell me who else
on my team is crooked?

283
00:17:38.684 --> 00:17:40.228
Sure.

284
00:17:40.311 --> 00:17:42.706
Roscoe checks out. 'cause
she dug in to get me out of prison.

285
00:17:42.730 --> 00:17:44.023
But you're hiding something.

286
00:17:44.106 --> 00:17:46.442
Tell me. why does
a Black cop from Boston

287
00:17:46.525 --> 00:17:49.237
with a 20-year pension come work
in a Southern backwater town

288
00:17:49.320 --> 00:17:50.613
in the middle of nowhere?

289
00:17:51.864 --> 00:17:53.449
You next in line for Morrison's job?

290
00:17:53.532 --> 00:17:55.719
For your information.
Mayor Teale didn't promote Finlay.

291
00:17:55.743 --> 00:17:57.370
He just appointed himself
acting chief.

292
00:17:57.828 --> 00:17:59.121
Since when?

293
00:17:59.205 --> 00:18:00.915
This morning. Came here to tell you.

294
00:18:01.374 --> 00:18:03.751
Whoever's running this
had Morrison under his thumb.

295
00:18:03.834 --> 00:18:05.103
No one sits in the chief's chair

296
00:18:05.127 --> 00:18:06.921
unless they're under it. too.

297
00:18:07.004 --> 00:18:08.381
They skipped you to get to Teale.

298
00:18:11.467 --> 00:18:13.278
So I guess that means
he's dirty and you're okay.

299
00:18:13.302 --> 00:18:16.222
Nothing means more to me
than your vote of confidence.

300
00:18:17.848 --> 00:18:20.393
But you're probably right.

301
00:18:20.476 --> 00:18:22.019
At least we know who we can trust.

302
00:18:23.938 --> 00:18:25.856
I'm gonna call my buddy at the FBI...

303
00:18:25.982 --> 00:18:28.109
Ah. Teale's first order was.
no staties. no Feds.

304
00:18:28.192 --> 00:18:29.485
He wants this kept in-house.

305
00:18:29.568 --> 00:18:32.405
Outside investigators will send
whoever did this into hiding.

306
00:18:32.488 --> 00:18:34.758
We'll let them think they've got it
under control for now.

307
00:18:34.782 --> 00:18:36.409
There's no "we" here.

308
00:18:39.245 --> 00:18:41.664
The Morrisons were killed
for a misstep.

309
00:18:41.747 --> 00:18:43.124
not pinning the murder on me.

310
00:18:43.207 --> 00:18:44.476
Hubble walking out of prison alive.

311
00:18:44.500 --> 00:18:45.978
but the way they were killed
sent a message

312
00:18:46.002 --> 00:18:47.003
to their organization.

313
00:18:47.086 --> 00:18:49.922
Don't screw up and don't cross us.

314
00:18:50.006 --> 00:18:51.366
You two think you can go it alone?

315
00:18:52.091 --> 00:18:53.175
You can't go it alone.

316
00:18:53.259 --> 00:18:54.343
There's only "we" here.

317
00:18:54.427 --> 00:18:57.221
You don't see that. I'll find
whoever killed Joe on my own.

318
00:19:02.393 --> 00:19:04.895
Great. Teale's called
an emergency town meeting.

319
00:19:04.979 --> 00:19:06.105
Be careful around him.

320
00:19:06.689 --> 00:19:08.983
Came down South for peace and quiet.

321
00:19:09.066 --> 00:19:10.609
Now I've caught four bodies.

322
00:19:10.693 --> 00:19:11.736
Five.

323
00:19:11.819 --> 00:19:13.696
Hubble. probably.

324
00:19:13.779 --> 00:19:16.657
If they'd do this to a cop.
why not a banker?

325
00:19:17.408 --> 00:19:18.409
Roscoe...

326
00:19:18.492 --> 00:19:19.702
On my way there now.

327
00:19:24.540 --> 00:19:26.834
Oh. I thought
you might've been Paul.

328
00:19:26.917 --> 00:19:28.145
That's why I left the gate open.

329
00:19:28.169 --> 00:19:29.170
He never came home?

330
00:19:29.253 --> 00:19:31.964
He called late last night.
said that he had to speak

331
00:19:32.048 --> 00:19:33.900
to some people about
sorting out this bank madness.

332
00:19:33.924 --> 00:19:36.427
and when I woke. I realized
he'd never come home.

333
00:19:36.510 --> 00:19:38.637
His phone goes to voice mail.

334
00:19:38.721 --> 00:19:41.015
Listen. I... I have been with Paul

335
00:19:41.098 --> 00:19:42.892
since freshman year. UGA.

336
00:19:42.975 --> 00:19:45.686
He has never once not come home.

337
00:19:46.270 --> 00:19:47.510
Okay. all right. just a minute.

338
00:19:48.856 --> 00:19:50.191
Um...

339
00:19:51.609 --> 00:19:53.069
I'll stay here since I'm armed.

340
00:19:53.152 --> 00:19:54.195
You go find Finlay.

341
00:19:54.278 --> 00:19:55.505
He'll know what to do with them.

342
00:19:55.529 --> 00:19:57.049
but they need some kind of protection.

343
00:19:59.784 --> 00:20:01.035
I need your car.

344
00:20:12.838 --> 00:20:15.508
You see anyone under six-five
come near this house...

345
00:20:15.591 --> 00:20:17.343
- shoot 'em.
- Finlay's five-eight.

346
00:20:17.426 --> 00:20:19.303
- Yup.
- Are you taking that knife?

347
00:20:19.387 --> 00:20:20.554
You want to give me your gun?

348
00:20:22.973 --> 00:20:24.517
That's what I thought.

349
00:20:26.018 --> 00:20:28.354
We will find
the person or persons

350
00:20:28.437 --> 00:20:29.939
responsible for these crimes.

351
00:20:30.022 --> 00:20:32.400
And we will punish them

352
00:20:32.483 --> 00:20:35.694
to the fullest extent of the law.

353
00:20:35.778 --> 00:20:37.905
If they're killing cops
in their own homes.

354
00:20:37.988 --> 00:20:39.740
then what chance do any of us got?

355
00:20:39.824 --> 00:20:42.827
A damn good chance.
Because as of today.

356
00:20:42.910 --> 00:20:45.454
per the powers given to me
by the town charter.

357
00:20:45.538 --> 00:20:48.874
I have appointed myself
chief of police.

358
00:20:48.958 --> 00:20:51.252
And I will not sleep

359
00:20:51.335 --> 00:20:54.171
until we have the perpetrators
behind bars

360
00:20:54.255 --> 00:20:56.674
and on their way
to getting the needle!

361
00:20:59.718 --> 00:21:01.262
But what the hell do you know

362
00:21:01.345 --> 00:21:03.514
- about law enforcement?
- That's right!

363
00:21:03.597 --> 00:21:05.015
We need us a real police chief

364
00:21:05.099 --> 00:21:06.475
and a real chief detective. too.

365
00:21:06.559 --> 00:21:08.978
- Yeah!
- Think he's talking about you.

366
00:21:09.061 --> 00:21:10.438
All due respect.

367
00:21:10.521 --> 00:21:12.898
but what does some Yankee cop
know about Margrave?

368
00:21:12.982 --> 00:21:14.042
- Yeah!
- That's right.

369
00:21:14.066 --> 00:21:15.985
We ain't seen a murder in 20 years.

370
00:21:16.068 --> 00:21:18.779
and now there's four...
Four. in two days.

371
00:21:19.530 --> 00:21:22.032
Do we have a serial killer
in Margrave or not?

372
00:21:22.408 --> 00:21:24.285
These killings are not related.

373
00:21:24.368 --> 00:21:27.037
Oh? What about that animal
you arrested out at the diner?

374
00:21:27.121 --> 00:21:28.723
- Yeah!
- I think she's talking about you.

375
00:21:28.747 --> 00:21:31.333
He comes to town.
and people just start dying?

376
00:21:31.417 --> 00:21:33.878
Y'all had him in jail.
Why'd you let him go?

377
00:21:33.961 --> 00:21:36.130
Order!

378
00:21:38.007 --> 00:21:39.967
Order!

379
00:21:40.050 --> 00:21:41.635
Everyone. please!

380
00:21:41.719 --> 00:21:44.263
Please. Calm down. Sit down.

381
00:21:44.346 --> 00:21:46.098
Sit down.

382
00:21:46.182 --> 00:21:48.517
I know you're all scared.

383
00:21:48.601 --> 00:21:51.395
But Mr. Reacher
has a rock-solid alibi.

384
00:21:51.812 --> 00:21:54.064
And for those of you who don't know.

385
00:21:54.148 --> 00:21:56.609
one of the victims was
Mr. Reacher's brother. Joseph.

386
00:21:57.610 --> 00:22:02.031
So he has as much invested in finding
these murderers as any one of us here.

387
00:22:04.241 --> 00:22:05.242
You know.

388
00:22:06.869 --> 00:22:10.122
when I moved Kliner Industries
to this town five years ago.

389
00:22:10.206 --> 00:22:12.958
Margrave was run-down.

390
00:22:13.042 --> 00:22:14.793
Broken.

391
00:22:14.877 --> 00:22:17.463
- Main Street boarded up. Right?
- Yeah.

392
00:22:17.546 --> 00:22:18.714
But I said to myself.

393
00:22:18.797 --> 00:22:22.384
these are the kind of people
who can bounce back.

394
00:22:22.468 --> 00:22:24.970
Right? Who can survive anything.

395
00:22:25.387 --> 00:22:27.473
I have faith in our police force.

396
00:22:27.556 --> 00:22:30.142
I have faith
in Chief Detective Finlay.

397
00:22:30.935 --> 00:22:33.187
I have faith
in our new chief of police.

398
00:22:33.270 --> 00:22:35.314
Mayor Teale.

399
00:22:35.397 --> 00:22:38.108
And I promise I will
provide whatever funds.

400
00:22:38.192 --> 00:22:42.404
whatever resources to find
whomever is responsible

401
00:22:42.488 --> 00:22:44.073
for these heinous acts.

402
00:22:45.157 --> 00:22:46.492
You have my word.

403
00:23:02.383 --> 00:23:03.592
Mayor Teale.

404
00:23:04.718 --> 00:23:05.719
A word?

405
00:23:07.596 --> 00:23:08.931
Chief Teale now. Captain.

406
00:23:09.014 --> 00:23:11.141
Mmm. Of course. My mistake.

407
00:23:12.393 --> 00:23:13.553
I just wanted to let you know

408
00:23:13.602 --> 00:23:15.482
that I'm gonna start
cross-referencing forensics

409
00:23:15.521 --> 00:23:17.856
from both murder sites
to establish pattern.

410
00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:20.317
Pattern? What the hell
has Morrison and his wife

411
00:23:20.401 --> 00:23:21.777
got to do with an out-of-towner

412
00:23:21.860 --> 00:23:24.047
and some fella he was probably
diddlin' under an overpass?

413
00:23:24.071 --> 00:23:25.298
Well. that's what I want to find out.

414
00:23:25.322 --> 00:23:27.157
These killings are not related.

415
00:23:27.241 --> 00:23:28.909
Over the course of his career.

416
00:23:28.993 --> 00:23:31.495
Morrison took countless
criminals out of circulation.

417
00:23:31.579 --> 00:23:33.163
Comb the archives.

418
00:23:33.247 --> 00:23:36.250
track down the biggest scumbags
he ever arrested

419
00:23:36.333 --> 00:23:38.502
who have since been released
or paroled. pardoned.

420
00:23:38.586 --> 00:23:39.920
everything in between...

421
00:23:40.004 --> 00:23:41.964
that's how you're gonna find
his killer.

422
00:23:42.047 --> 00:23:43.299
Those are your orders.

423
00:23:43.382 --> 00:23:44.466
You copy. Captain?

424
00:23:45.926 --> 00:23:47.344
And the bodies by the highway?

425
00:23:47.428 --> 00:23:49.096
A police officer was crucified!

426
00:23:51.557 --> 00:23:53.392
I think that takes priority.

427
00:23:54.727 --> 00:23:57.396
Or did they do things differently
up there in Massachusetts?

428
00:23:58.731 --> 00:24:00.065
Hmm?

429
00:24:00.149 --> 00:24:01.275
Copy that.

430
00:24:11.452 --> 00:24:14.997
Teale's trying to frame
the Morrison hit as a revenge killing.

431
00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:17.249
Just sent me off to chase my tail.

432
00:24:17.333 --> 00:24:18.751
Told you he's dirty.

433
00:24:18.834 --> 00:24:19.960
I'm prone to agree.

434
00:24:20.044 --> 00:24:21.879
but incompetence
can look like malevolence.

435
00:24:21.962 --> 00:24:23.547
and it's a whole lot more common.

436
00:24:23.631 --> 00:24:25.299
You know who's not incompetent?

437
00:24:25.382 --> 00:24:26.425
Kliner.

438
00:24:29.303 --> 00:24:31.722
You one of those conspiracy nuts?

439
00:24:31.805 --> 00:24:33.891
Guys with the kind of money
and power Kliner wields

440
00:24:33.974 --> 00:24:35.351
are rarely angels.

441
00:24:35.434 --> 00:24:36.560
We need to look into him.

442
00:24:36.644 --> 00:24:38.979
You want this town to hate you
more than it already does?

443
00:24:39.063 --> 00:24:40.790
Then start smearing Kliner.
And I'm not gonna be able

444
00:24:40.814 --> 00:24:42.524
to look into anyone except the losers

445
00:24:42.608 --> 00:24:44.151
in Morrison's old case files.

446
00:24:44.234 --> 00:24:46.987
No. that's what you'll pretend to do.
Roscoe. too.

447
00:24:47.071 --> 00:24:49.239
Give us cover while
we work the real angles.

448
00:24:49.323 --> 00:24:51.033
Like Joe's rental car.

449
00:24:51.116 --> 00:24:53.356
Must have had one. but none was left
at the murder scene.

450
00:24:54.411 --> 00:24:56.205
You're handing out assignments now?

451
00:24:56.288 --> 00:24:59.792
Yes. And the next one has to do
with Hubble's wife and kids.

452
00:24:59.875 --> 00:25:02.795
They need protection.
even if Hubble's already dead.

453
00:25:02.878 --> 00:25:04.314
These guys get antsy.
think Charlie has

454
00:25:04.338 --> 00:25:06.215
even a 1% chance
of knowing anything...

455
00:25:06.298 --> 00:25:08.258
I get it.

456
00:25:08.342 --> 00:25:12.054
My FBI buddy I wanted
to reach out to earlier...

457
00:25:12.137 --> 00:25:14.640
Name's Picard. Atlanta field office.

458
00:25:14.723 --> 00:25:16.308
I'll call you when it's set up.

459
00:25:16.392 --> 00:25:18.560
- I don't have a phone.
- Get one.

460
00:25:18.644 --> 00:25:19.895
Can we trust Picard?

461
00:25:20.771 --> 00:25:22.189
Known him for years.

462
00:25:22.272 --> 00:25:24.233
Gave me the best advice I ever got.

463
00:25:25.359 --> 00:25:27.069
Don't take the Margrave job.

464
00:25:32.991 --> 00:25:34.284
Mr. Reacher?

465
00:25:34.868 --> 00:25:37.746
I'd like to offer my apologies
for your arrest.

466
00:25:37.830 --> 00:25:40.457
My condolences for your brother.

467
00:25:40.541 --> 00:25:44.461
Tragedy when a person is struck down
in his prime like that.

468
00:25:44.545 --> 00:25:46.797
But my hand to God.
we'll find the killer.

469
00:25:49.758 --> 00:25:51.969
We'd be happy to keep you
updated on the investigation.

470
00:25:52.052 --> 00:25:53.470
Just leave your contact information

471
00:25:53.554 --> 00:25:55.222
with the department
before you head out.

472
00:25:55.305 --> 00:25:57.558
- I'm not leaving.
- Oh.

473
00:25:57.641 --> 00:25:59.619
It was my understanding
you were just passing through.

474
00:25:59.643 --> 00:26:00.811
You understood wrong.

475
00:26:01.353 --> 00:26:03.063
I figured I'd stick around a while.

476
00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:05.733
Margrave's such a nice town.

477
00:26:07.568 --> 00:26:08.902
Used to be.

478
00:26:10.738 --> 00:26:12.448
Not so much lately.

479
00:26:21.999 --> 00:26:24.126
Heard about your brother.

480
00:26:24.209 --> 00:26:26.211
May the Lord bless him

481
00:26:26.295 --> 00:26:28.589
and keep him in a plastic container.

482
00:26:30.257 --> 00:26:31.884
You looking for payback?

483
00:26:31.967 --> 00:26:34.219
Payback. justice. vengeance.

484
00:26:35.429 --> 00:26:36.847
Looking for the whole gang.

485
00:26:38.140 --> 00:26:39.767
You might not be the only one.

486
00:26:40.559 --> 00:26:41.935
- Meaning?
- Meaning.

487
00:26:42.019 --> 00:26:43.353
you wouldn't happen to have

488
00:26:43.437 --> 00:26:46.523
a couple of Spanish-speaking
amigos in town. would you?

489
00:26:46.940 --> 00:26:48.650
- No.
- Makes sense.

490
00:26:48.734 --> 00:26:51.779
'Cause the two fellas come by
my shop asking about you

491
00:26:51.862 --> 00:26:54.239
didn't seem all that friendly.

492
00:26:54.323 --> 00:26:56.408
Watch your back. Mr. Reacher.

493
00:26:56.825 --> 00:26:58.535
Are you worried about me. Mr. Mosley?

494
00:26:59.495 --> 00:27:01.330
Worried about my bottom line.

495
00:27:02.289 --> 00:27:06.084
Uh. you might need another shave
'fore you leave town.

496
00:27:06.168 --> 00:27:08.212
Very true.

497
00:27:08.295 --> 00:27:10.172
<i>My husband trusted Reacher.</i>

498
00:27:10.714 --> 00:27:11.965
Is he a good person?

499
00:27:15.677 --> 00:27:16.678
I think so.

500
00:27:18.347 --> 00:27:20.849
We don't really have the luxury
of certainty right now. but...

501
00:27:21.767 --> 00:27:24.561
bad things are happening
and Reacher can help us.

502
00:27:24.645 --> 00:27:26.438
I'm back.

503
00:27:27.481 --> 00:27:28.482
We're in here.

504
00:27:30.234 --> 00:27:32.319
Get some food together.
pack your bags for the kids.

505
00:27:32.402 --> 00:27:34.238
- Where we going?
- Got a call from Finlay.

506
00:27:34.321 --> 00:27:36.740
FBI agent named Picard is on his way.

507
00:27:36.824 --> 00:27:38.384
He's taking you
into protective custody.

508
00:27:38.909 --> 00:27:39.910
I bought a burner.

509
00:27:40.536 --> 00:27:41.954
Here's the number.

510
00:27:42.037 --> 00:27:45.165
I'd feel safer if we stayed
with the two of you.

511
00:27:45.249 --> 00:27:46.458
We've got to work the case.

512
00:27:46.542 --> 00:27:48.168
Picard'll keep you safe.

513
00:27:48.252 --> 00:27:49.852
It's what your husband
would have wanted.

514
00:27:51.213 --> 00:27:53.093
Why are you talking
about him in the past tense?

515
00:28:01.139 --> 00:28:02.558
We have to assume Paul's dead.

516
00:28:02.641 --> 00:28:04.059
They tried to kill him in prison.

517
00:28:04.142 --> 00:28:05.978
They killed Morrison and his wife.

518
00:28:06.061 --> 00:28:07.121
Your husband's gone missing.

519
00:28:07.145 --> 00:28:08.939
so they most likely killed him. too.

520
00:28:09.022 --> 00:28:10.342
There'll be time to grieve later.

521
00:28:10.399 --> 00:28:11.759
You have to think about your kids.

522
00:28:13.193 --> 00:28:14.611
You need to pack.

523
00:28:15.821 --> 00:28:16.822
Okay?

524
00:28:16.905 --> 00:28:18.949
- Okay?
- Okay. okay.

525
00:28:27.082 --> 00:28:28.750
I'll go wait for Picard.

526
00:28:49.146 --> 00:28:50.790
<i>Dance! Dance! Dance! Dance!</i>

527
00:28:50.814 --> 00:28:52.941
Dance! Dance! Dance! Dance!

528
00:28:54.693 --> 00:28:56.486
Let's go. Billy! Dance!

529
00:28:56.570 --> 00:28:57.696
Dance! Dance!

530
00:28:59.573 --> 00:29:01.867
Okay. Mr. Predicto.

531
00:29:01.950 --> 00:29:03.869
should Billy keep dancing?

532
00:29:05.287 --> 00:29:06.955
"All signs indicate yes."

533
00:29:07.039 --> 00:29:08.749
Come on. man!

534
00:29:11.168 --> 00:29:12.169
Hey!

535
00:29:17.591 --> 00:29:19.134
You boys looking for a dance partner?

536
00:29:20.218 --> 00:29:22.095
You think you can take all of us?

537
00:29:25.307 --> 00:29:26.558
Let's find out.

538
00:29:28.435 --> 00:29:30.595
It's Billy's dad! Go. go. go. go!

539
00:30:05.764 --> 00:30:06.765
We're on the move.

540
00:30:06.848 --> 00:30:08.600
It's not safe anymore. Let's go.

541
00:30:08.684 --> 00:30:10.143
- I'm not ready.
- Let's go. Now.

542
00:30:11.520 --> 00:30:12.646
Girls!

543
00:30:13.772 --> 00:30:15.399
Lucy. come get your backpack.

544
00:30:18.151 --> 00:30:20.362
Okay. you got everything
you need. right?

545
00:30:23.448 --> 00:30:25.367
Hey. hey. hey. Easy.

546
00:30:26.034 --> 00:30:27.160
I'm Picard.

547
00:30:33.083 --> 00:30:34.710
Mind putting the cannon down?

548
00:30:40.966 --> 00:30:42.300
Told you I need my own gun.

549
00:30:44.928 --> 00:30:46.304
I'll get the bags.

550
00:30:46.388 --> 00:30:48.223
All right. Come on. girls. come on.

551
00:30:49.599 --> 00:30:50.600
Hop in.

552
00:30:52.060 --> 00:30:54.312
Here. help your sister
with her seat belt.

553
00:30:55.397 --> 00:30:58.025
- Got it?
- Okay. this is off the books.

554
00:30:58.108 --> 00:31:00.193
To get a family into an actual
protection program

555
00:31:00.277 --> 00:31:01.778
would take time and red tape.

556
00:31:01.862 --> 00:31:04.114
Finlay said he can't get
the FBI officially involved yet.

557
00:31:04.197 --> 00:31:05.907
so I'm gonna take a few personal days.

558
00:31:05.991 --> 00:31:07.451
watch the family myself.

559
00:31:07.534 --> 00:31:10.328
Bottom line. do not let this
bite me in the ass.

560
00:31:10.412 --> 00:31:12.831
We are talking about my career here.

561
00:31:12.914 --> 00:31:14.875
Finlay and I are tight.
we ain't that tight.

562
00:31:14.958 --> 00:31:16.209
We won't let you get burned.

563
00:31:16.293 --> 00:31:17.711
Better not.

564
00:31:22.049 --> 00:31:23.759
I told him not to take this job.

565
00:31:29.264 --> 00:31:30.974
Now we get to work.

566
00:31:31.058 --> 00:31:33.745
I'm gonna make some calls. find out
what Joe was doing with Homeland.

567
00:31:33.769 --> 00:31:35.289
You're gonna have to do it
on the side.

568
00:31:35.353 --> 00:31:36.748
Teale's got everyone on a snipe hunt.

569
00:31:36.772 --> 00:31:38.023
- Finlay'll fill you in.
- Okay.

570
00:31:38.106 --> 00:31:39.107
What about you?

571
00:31:39.191 --> 00:31:41.276
I'm gonna go see that guard
Spivey at Warburton.

572
00:31:41.359 --> 00:31:43.087
Whoever paid him
to set up Hubble to be killed

573
00:31:43.111 --> 00:31:46.073
is who's running this thing.
Spivey's the key.

574
00:31:46.156 --> 00:31:47.491
He won't tell you anything.

575
00:31:48.492 --> 00:31:49.826
Depends on how I ask.

576
00:31:58.752 --> 00:31:59.795
Taylor Spivey.

577
00:31:59.878 --> 00:32:01.630
Chief Detective Finlay. Margrave PD.

578
00:32:01.713 --> 00:32:03.590
Calling on account of Jack Reacher.

579
00:32:04.132 --> 00:32:06.093
Yeah. well. he's pissed.

580
00:32:06.176 --> 00:32:08.345
Says he got tuned up
pretty good while under your roof.

581
00:32:08.428 --> 00:32:09.471
and now he's suing.

582
00:32:10.347 --> 00:32:11.681
Well. he was your prisoner.

583
00:32:11.765 --> 00:32:14.601
and I'm not losing my job over this.

584
00:32:14.684 --> 00:32:16.686
Is there somewhere we can meet up.

585
00:32:16.770 --> 00:32:19.523
get our stories straight
before lawyers start sniffing around?

586
00:32:22.818 --> 00:32:23.860
Okay.

587
00:32:26.321 --> 00:32:28.031
See you there. jackass.

588
00:32:37.999 --> 00:32:40.127
Hey. Spivey.

589
00:32:40.210 --> 00:32:42.546
Eh. look who it is.

590
00:32:42.629 --> 00:32:45.006
You know.
I never met Detective Finlay.

591
00:32:46.049 --> 00:32:47.801
but I heard all about him.

592
00:32:47.884 --> 00:32:50.844
And you sure as hell don't sound like
a Black man from Boston on the phone.

593
00:32:52.347 --> 00:32:53.723
Figured you were setting me up.

594
00:32:53.807 --> 00:32:56.768
so I thought I'd return the favor.

595
00:33:01.273 --> 00:33:03.650
You should've let those boys
kill you in the prison.

596
00:33:04.860 --> 00:33:07.237
It would've been a lot less painful.

597
00:33:07.320 --> 00:33:08.572
Adios.

598
00:33:16.371 --> 00:33:17.414
Let's go.

599
00:33:23.712 --> 00:33:24.713
No.

600
00:33:26.423 --> 00:33:27.841
It's too small.

601
00:33:27.924 --> 00:33:29.384
It'll be uncomfortable.

602
00:33:29.467 --> 00:33:32.012
Not as uncomfortable as
a bullet to the stomach. <i>pendejo.</i>

603
00:33:33.096 --> 00:33:35.116
Well. the smart move
would be to shoot me right here.

604
00:33:35.140 --> 00:33:36.892
but you haven't done that yet.

605
00:33:36.975 --> 00:33:38.286
Maybe you don't want to draw attention

606
00:33:38.310 --> 00:33:40.937
firing outside a crowded bar.

607
00:33:41.021 --> 00:33:42.981
Or maybe you have orders
to take me to your boss

608
00:33:43.064 --> 00:33:44.464
so he can find out how much I know.

609
00:33:47.736 --> 00:33:50.071
Whatever it is. it means
that when I make my move.

610
00:33:50.155 --> 00:33:51.198
you're gonna hesitate.

611
00:33:51.823 --> 00:33:54.576
And you guys know what Cato
said about hesitation. right?

612
00:33:56.203 --> 00:33:57.662
"He who hesitates..."

613
00:34:06.838 --> 00:34:08.465
<i>Puta.</i> I'm gonna cut you.

614
00:34:39.246 --> 00:34:41.206
Stop where you are!

615
00:34:41.289 --> 00:34:43.291
This is Mike-7.
I need backup at the Blue Cat.

616
00:34:43.416 --> 00:34:46.086
Foot pursuit of one suspect.
Second at large.

617
00:34:52.759 --> 00:34:55.470
All right. yep. Thank you.

618
00:34:55.553 --> 00:34:57.097
Bye. now.

619
00:34:57.180 --> 00:34:59.766
Both Avis and Hertz confirmed.
no unaccounted-for

620
00:34:59.849 --> 00:35:01.559
rental cars in the entire state.

621
00:35:02.394 --> 00:35:05.021
How many more are we
waiting on answers from. six?

622
00:35:05.105 --> 00:35:07.065
In the Atlanta airport alone.

623
00:35:10.735 --> 00:35:11.987
It didn't go as planned.

624
00:35:14.072 --> 00:35:15.073
Well...

625
00:35:17.450 --> 00:35:18.743
this one's special.

626
00:35:18.827 --> 00:35:20.161
You need stitches.

627
00:35:20.245 --> 00:35:21.246
No. I don't.

628
00:35:23.832 --> 00:35:25.959
Fine. Superglue it is.

629
00:35:26.042 --> 00:35:29.838
Just got off the phone
with the Georgia State Police.

630
00:35:29.921 --> 00:35:33.550
No suspects from the Blue Cat brawl
were apprehended.

631
00:35:33.633 --> 00:35:35.677
Would've been nice to question them.

632
00:35:35.760 --> 00:35:38.888
Maybe next time. don't pull something
like this by yourself.

633
00:35:38.972 --> 00:35:40.724
I said you could work with us.

634
00:35:41.099 --> 00:35:43.018
It's not my fault
Spivey didn't buy it.

635
00:35:43.101 --> 00:35:45.061
I shoved a pole as far up my ass
as I could.

636
00:35:45.145 --> 00:35:46.896
I still couldn't sound like you.

637
00:35:46.980 --> 00:35:49.024
You've been here a couple
of days and you've already

638
00:35:49.107 --> 00:35:51.693
thrown down in Warburton.
beaten up some locals

639
00:35:51.776 --> 00:35:53.546
and fought a couple of goons
in a parking lot.

640
00:35:53.570 --> 00:35:55.071
They weren't goons.

641
00:35:55.155 --> 00:35:56.823
Probably military. or ex-military.

642
00:35:57.198 --> 00:35:59.367
- South American.
- How could you know that?

643
00:35:59.451 --> 00:36:01.846
'Cause if they weren't I would've
killed them within ten seconds.

644
00:36:01.870 --> 00:36:04.039
How'd you know they were
South American military?

645
00:36:04.122 --> 00:36:06.041
Spoke Spanish. had Glock-17s

646
00:36:06.124 --> 00:36:07.685
and the technique one guy
used to head-butt me

647
00:36:07.709 --> 00:36:09.145
was from a martial art called Reisy.

648
00:36:09.169 --> 00:36:10.879
Hardly anyone uses except branches of

649
00:36:10.962 --> 00:36:12.505
South American special forces.

650
00:36:14.299 --> 00:36:16.859
Plus. if they weren't. I would've
killed them within ten seconds.

651
00:36:17.135 --> 00:36:19.554
Why would South American
military be involved in this?

652
00:36:19.637 --> 00:36:20.638
Don't know.

653
00:36:20.722 --> 00:36:22.408
You ever see anyone
like that around Margrave?

654
00:36:22.432 --> 00:36:24.267
Not till you showed up.

655
00:36:24.351 --> 00:36:26.436
Then they're hired muscle.
Not running the show.

656
00:36:26.519 --> 00:36:27.645
You're all set.

657
00:36:27.729 --> 00:36:30.940
I have no idea what the hell's
going on around here.

658
00:36:31.024 --> 00:36:32.525
Well. I might. if you're done talking

659
00:36:32.609 --> 00:36:34.361
about Spivey
and South American military.

660
00:36:34.444 --> 00:36:37.280
Turns out Joe was working for
the Secret Services division

661
00:36:37.364 --> 00:36:38.865
- of Homeland.
- Doing what?

662
00:36:38.948 --> 00:36:40.801
No one could or would
give me any answers. but...

663
00:36:40.825 --> 00:36:44.621
Secret Service covers everything from
mail fraud to protecting the president

664
00:36:44.704 --> 00:36:46.456
to child exploitation.

665
00:36:46.539 --> 00:36:49.084
Your brother could've been
involved in almost anything.

666
00:36:49.167 --> 00:36:52.337
Counterfeiting? Hubble specialized
in currency management.

667
00:36:52.420 --> 00:36:53.421
Yeah. maybe.

668
00:36:53.505 --> 00:36:55.274
But money's at the root
of every crime there is.

669
00:36:55.298 --> 00:36:57.384
Drugs. guns. human trafficking...

670
00:36:57.467 --> 00:36:59.803
- all rotates around cash.
- Well...

671
00:36:59.886 --> 00:37:02.639
I left a voice mail with
the Office of Investigations.

672
00:37:02.722 --> 00:37:04.700
Figure people usually get hurt
when they're looking

673
00:37:04.724 --> 00:37:07.310
into something others
don't want 'em to. assumed maybe

674
00:37:07.394 --> 00:37:09.270
Joe was an investigator like you.

675
00:37:09.729 --> 00:37:10.730
Good logic.

676
00:37:13.400 --> 00:37:14.484
Thanks. Doc.

677
00:37:14.901 --> 00:37:16.181
Where do you think you're going?

678
00:37:16.986 --> 00:37:18.798
Homeland Security won't
call back till tomorrow

679
00:37:18.822 --> 00:37:21.133
and by now Spivey's heard things
have gone sideways at the bar.

680
00:37:21.157 --> 00:37:23.368
Since his bosses feed screwups
their own testicles.

681
00:37:23.451 --> 00:37:26.454
my guess is he's gotten
out of Dodge for a while.

682
00:37:26.538 --> 00:37:27.973
I'm gonna find his house
and search it.

683
00:37:27.997 --> 00:37:29.934
Prison guard's
home address won't be public.

684
00:37:29.958 --> 00:37:32.669
And county offices
won't be open till morning.

685
00:37:32.752 --> 00:37:35.338
I'll chase it down then
and handle it myself.

686
00:37:35.422 --> 00:37:36.423
You?

687
00:37:37.549 --> 00:37:38.550
Go get some rest.

688
00:37:39.968 --> 00:37:42.220
- I'm getting a beer.
- Absolutely not.

689
00:37:42.303 --> 00:37:43.805
You saw those people at town hall.

690
00:37:43.888 --> 00:37:45.032
They were ready to grab torches

691
00:37:45.056 --> 00:37:46.933
and come after you like Frankenstein.

692
00:37:47.016 --> 00:37:48.977
Frankenstein was the doctor.

693
00:37:49.060 --> 00:37:50.979
They went after
Frankenstein's monster.

694
00:37:52.105 --> 00:37:53.106
Details matter.

695
00:37:54.566 --> 00:37:56.443
You're going back to your motel.

696
00:37:57.193 --> 00:37:59.028
I'm just gonna sit in a bar.

697
00:37:59.112 --> 00:38:01.114
have a beer
and think all this through.

698
00:38:01.197 --> 00:38:03.408
And then someone will say
something you don't like

699
00:38:03.491 --> 00:38:05.452
and you'll break
their head open... again.

700
00:38:06.286 --> 00:38:07.745
Not gonna happen.

701
00:38:07.829 --> 00:38:10.081
Now you can go to your motel
right now and sleep

702
00:38:10.165 --> 00:38:12.667
in a comfortable bed.
or I can arrest you for vagrancy

703
00:38:12.750 --> 00:38:14.794
and you can sleep in my holding cell.

704
00:38:14.878 --> 00:38:16.838
He's not a vagrant. He's a hobo.

705
00:38:18.965 --> 00:38:19.966
What?

706
00:38:28.600 --> 00:38:29.601
Just tail him.

707
00:38:29.684 --> 00:38:32.145
Make sure he goes
straight back to the motel.

708
00:38:44.699 --> 00:38:46.951
Hey. I get it.

709
00:38:47.035 --> 00:38:49.871
In the past few days. you've lost
one brother and had four fights.

710
00:38:49.954 --> 00:38:51.372
If anybody needs a drink. it's you.

711
00:38:57.128 --> 00:38:58.755
There's a roadhouse.

712
00:38:58.838 --> 00:39:00.507
Just across the border in Alabama.

713
00:39:00.590 --> 00:39:02.258
Nobody knows you there.

714
00:39:02.342 --> 00:39:04.511
Cold beer. hot music.

715
00:39:05.553 --> 00:39:06.804
But you got to behave.

716
00:39:09.891 --> 00:39:12.227
Maybe they'll even play
that blues stuff you like.

717
00:39:16.147 --> 00:39:17.148
Okay.

718
00:39:18.066 --> 00:39:19.359
Follow me to my place.

719
00:39:19.442 --> 00:39:22.320
I got to change into something
less "law enforcement."

720
00:39:22.403 --> 00:39:23.839
And we got to stop by a gas station.

721
00:39:23.863 --> 00:39:25.943
and get you a T-shirt
with a little less blood on it.

722
00:39:28.034 --> 00:39:29.744
<i>You're listening to WGUT.</i>

723
00:39:29.827 --> 00:39:31.454
<i>blues that hit you right in the gut.</i>

724
00:39:31.538 --> 00:39:33.873
<i>Here's "Police Dog Blues"
by Cephas & Wiggins.</i>

725
00:39:33.957 --> 00:39:37.669
<i>originally recorded by
the late. great Blind Blake.</i>

726
00:39:37.752 --> 00:39:40.352
Hey. isn't that your guy. Blake?

727
00:39:40.463 --> 00:39:42.549
Yep.

728
00:39:42.632 --> 00:39:44.300
<i>All my life I've been</i>

729
00:39:44.425 --> 00:39:45.468
Nice.

730
00:39:45.552 --> 00:39:48.137
<i>A travelin' man</i>

731
00:39:48.221 --> 00:39:51.724
<i>Stayin' alone
and doin' the best I can</i>

732
00:39:55.728 --> 00:39:59.524
<i>We did it deep
and we did it long</i>

733
00:40:00.900 --> 00:40:04.654
<i>I was ready
and she was strong</i>

734
00:40:04.737 --> 00:40:05.989
Thanks.

735
00:40:06.072 --> 00:40:08.825
<i>Wait. she said. slow it down</i>

736
00:40:08.908 --> 00:40:10.326
It's not a twist-off.

737
00:40:10.410 --> 00:40:13.496
<i>Till you hear that
engine go through town...</i>

738
00:40:16.374 --> 00:40:17.584
Show off.

739
00:40:31.222 --> 00:40:32.265
Feeling any better?

740
00:40:33.474 --> 00:40:34.642
Not feeling worse.

741
00:40:36.936 --> 00:40:38.438
Well. that's a start. ain't it?

742
00:40:45.570 --> 00:40:46.613
Uh-oh.

743
00:40:47.572 --> 00:40:49.240
They're playin' Patsy.

744
00:40:49.324 --> 00:40:50.658
You know what that means.

745
00:40:50.742 --> 00:40:52.201
No.

746
00:40:52.285 --> 00:40:53.411
<i>I'm crazy...</i>

747
00:40:53.494 --> 00:40:55.580
Means we got to dance.
Practically the law.

748
00:40:56.789 --> 00:40:58.333
I don't dance.

749
00:40:58.416 --> 00:40:59.959
You're telling me that your mama

750
00:41:00.043 --> 00:41:01.794
never taught her sons how to dance?

751
00:41:01.878 --> 00:41:04.464
She did. but when I ask
people to dance.

752
00:41:04.547 --> 00:41:06.466
it usually precedes a lot of punching.

753
00:41:06.549 --> 00:41:08.760
Good thing I'm doing the asking.

754
00:41:09.177 --> 00:41:10.637
Come on...

755
00:41:10.720 --> 00:41:13.806
Frankenstein's monster.

756
00:41:16.601 --> 00:41:19.103
<i>I knew</i>

757
00:41:19.187 --> 00:41:21.648
<i>You'd love me as long</i>

758
00:41:21.731 --> 00:41:25.026
<i>As you wanted</i>

759
00:41:28.446 --> 00:41:32.450
<i>And then someday</i>

760
00:41:32.533 --> 00:41:37.705
<i>You'd leave me for somebody new</i>

761
00:41:42.585 --> 00:41:44.712
<i>Worry</i>

762
00:41:46.297 --> 00:41:51.469
<i>Why do I let myself worry</i>

763
00:41:56.349 --> 00:41:58.434
<i>Wondering</i>

764
00:41:59.686 --> 00:42:02.689
<i>What in the world</i>

765
00:42:02.772 --> 00:42:05.858
<i>Did I do?</i>

766
00:42:08.778 --> 00:42:12.031
<i>Oh. crazy</i>

767
00:42:13.074 --> 00:42:17.161
<i>For thinking that my love</i>

768
00:42:17.245 --> 00:42:21.082
<i>Could hold you</i>

769
00:42:24.377 --> 00:42:25.461
Oh!

770
00:42:30.717 --> 00:42:32.593
I-I don't need your jacket.

771
00:42:34.762 --> 00:42:36.973
Move your ass. big guy.

772
00:42:50.319 --> 00:42:52.530
You should've taken my jacket.

773
00:42:54.073 --> 00:42:55.408
I'm a big girl.

774
00:43:00.747 --> 00:43:02.790
Whoa. look at this.

775
00:43:06.502 --> 00:43:07.962
Hey. take a beat. champ.

776
00:43:08.045 --> 00:43:09.839
We're far from Margrave.

777
00:43:09.922 --> 00:43:11.424
Not far enough.

778
00:43:11.507 --> 00:43:12.717
I say go. you duck.

779
00:43:40.620 --> 00:43:41.662
What's goin' on?

780
00:43:41.746 --> 00:43:44.248
Road east to the highway's flooded.

781
00:43:44.332 --> 00:43:46.000
No one's getting through tonight.

782
00:43:52.632 --> 00:43:53.800
Is there a motel near here?

783
00:44:04.352 --> 00:44:07.021
Sorry I didn't have anything
in my truck your size.

784
00:44:07.688 --> 00:44:09.816
Could've sworn I had a paint tarp

785
00:44:09.899 --> 00:44:11.567
or a circus tent.

786
00:44:12.443 --> 00:44:14.487
Funny.

787
00:44:14.570 --> 00:44:16.572
I got a sampling from
the vending machine.

788
00:44:17.156 --> 00:44:18.157
Wow.

789
00:44:20.076 --> 00:44:22.411
- You always eat this well?
- I was hungry.

790
00:44:22.495 --> 00:44:24.622
Didn't think room service
would deliver this late.

791
00:44:24.705 --> 00:44:25.832
Hmm.

792
00:44:26.958 --> 00:44:28.584
Oh. yeah.

793
00:44:28.668 --> 00:44:31.087
Going straight for the Clark Bar.

794
00:44:31.170 --> 00:44:33.881
Clark Bars are the best.

795
00:44:33.965 --> 00:44:35.716
Had these at every PX on every base

796
00:44:35.800 --> 00:44:38.135
I ever lived at when I was a kid.

797
00:44:38.219 --> 00:44:40.638
No matter where we were
at the time. Joe and I could always

798
00:44:40.721 --> 00:44:41.889
find a Clark Bar.

799
00:44:45.226 --> 00:44:46.519
- You want half?
- No.

800
00:44:46.602 --> 00:44:48.104
Prefer Zagnut.

801
00:44:48.187 --> 00:44:49.730
No one prefers Zagnut.

802
00:44:50.773 --> 00:44:52.650
- Excuse me?
- What are you eating right now?

803
00:44:52.733 --> 00:44:53.818
Read me the flavor.

804
00:44:53.901 --> 00:44:55.486
Spi...

805
00:44:55.570 --> 00:44:56.821
Read it out loud.

806
00:44:57.280 --> 00:44:58.739
"Spicy Cajun Crawtators."

807
00:44:58.823 --> 00:45:00.700
There you go.

808
00:45:00.783 --> 00:45:02.118
I'll take a Clark Bar.

809
00:45:08.332 --> 00:45:09.584
You okay down there?

810
00:45:11.419 --> 00:45:12.879
I've slept in worse places.

811
00:45:15.965 --> 00:45:17.216
Been all over. huh?

812
00:45:18.634 --> 00:45:20.219
Barely left Margrave.

813
00:45:22.096 --> 00:45:23.139
Never really wanted to.

814
00:45:25.141 --> 00:45:27.643
My family's been here
since the town was founded.

815
00:45:28.728 --> 00:45:30.563
Like the Teales.

816
00:45:30.646 --> 00:45:32.481
Fuck the Teales.

817
00:45:32.565 --> 00:45:34.650
Conklins built this town.
Teales stole it.

818
00:45:34.734 --> 00:45:38.362
Old Casper Teale got in bed
with the railroads.

819
00:45:38.446 --> 00:45:40.114
Swindled farmers out of their land

820
00:45:40.197 --> 00:45:43.200
and laid tracks
right through their crops.

821
00:45:43.284 --> 00:45:45.578
You still have family in Margrave?

822
00:45:46.120 --> 00:45:47.663
My parents died when I was a kid.

823
00:45:48.331 --> 00:45:49.916
But I had Gray.

824
00:45:50.750 --> 00:45:51.918
Gray?

825
00:45:52.001 --> 00:45:53.961
Had Finlay's job before Finlay.

826
00:45:55.463 --> 00:45:58.007
He was my parents' best friend.

827
00:46:01.260 --> 00:46:04.263
Always looked out for me.

828
00:46:04.388 --> 00:46:06.265
Kind of like a second dad.

829
00:46:06.349 --> 00:46:08.392
Taught me everything I know
about being a cop.

830
00:46:08.517 --> 00:46:13.856
How to work a case.
keep your notes and files organized.

831
00:46:13.940 --> 00:46:16.150
He was the most

832
00:46:16.233 --> 00:46:18.903
fastidious person I have ever met.

833
00:46:20.655 --> 00:46:22.490
I mean. the man only had
a horseshoe of hair.

834
00:46:22.573 --> 00:46:24.617
and he still had Mosley
trim it for him once a week.

835
00:46:27.536 --> 00:46:29.330
But he had a dark side. too.

836
00:46:31.749 --> 00:46:34.669
He was depressed a lot.

837
00:46:35.586 --> 00:46:36.879
Never married.

838
00:46:36.963 --> 00:46:38.339
No kids. Drank.

839
00:46:41.092 --> 00:46:44.720
Hung himself from the rafters
in his garage about a year ago.

840
00:46:46.138 --> 00:46:47.139
I'm sorry.

841
00:46:48.599 --> 00:46:50.393
Always gave me daisies on my birthday.

842
00:46:53.020 --> 00:46:54.397
Daisies are my favorite.

843
00:46:56.357 --> 00:46:57.650
What about you?

844
00:46:57.733 --> 00:46:59.276
Snapdragons.

845
00:47:00.820 --> 00:47:02.363
Cool name. hard to kill.

846
00:47:03.739 --> 00:47:05.658
Yeah. yeah.

847
00:47:05.741 --> 00:47:08.452
That sounds like somebody I know.

848
00:47:08.536 --> 00:47:10.496
No. that wasn't what I was asking you.

849
00:47:10.579 --> 00:47:12.498
I was...

850
00:47:12.581 --> 00:47:15.042
I was wondering if you had
any family I didn't know about?

851
00:47:15.126 --> 00:47:18.546
No. Was basically down to Joe.

852
00:47:18.629 --> 00:47:19.714
Hmm.

853
00:47:22.466 --> 00:47:24.277
If I hadn't have walked
in that bar a few days ago.

854
00:47:24.301 --> 00:47:25.720
heard that Blind Blake song.

855
00:47:25.803 --> 00:47:28.180
probably would've been years
before I found out he was dead.

856
00:47:30.683 --> 00:47:33.769
Well. in spite of the circumstances...

857
00:47:37.231 --> 00:47:38.858
...it's been nice getting to know you.

858
00:47:40.526 --> 00:47:42.278
Nice getting to know you. too.

859
00:47:43.446 --> 00:47:44.989
Night. Reacher.

860
00:47:49.827 --> 00:47:51.454
Good night. Roscoe.

861
00:48:26.280 --> 00:48:27.615
You know. before we get into it.

862
00:48:27.698 --> 00:48:29.283
I could use a real breakfast.

863
00:48:29.366 --> 00:48:30.910
That Zagnut ain't cuttin' it.

864
00:48:31.494 --> 00:48:32.828
Should've had the Clark Bar.

865
00:48:32.912 --> 00:48:34.663
Yeah?

866
00:49:17.790 --> 00:49:18.833
All clear.

867
00:49:21.585 --> 00:49:23.045
Clear.

868
00:49:24.130 --> 00:49:27.007
When they came in. they tracked
through the flower bed.

869
00:49:27.091 --> 00:49:28.509
Rubber overshoes.

870
00:49:30.052 --> 00:49:31.387
They were gonna kill me?

871
00:49:31.470 --> 00:49:33.931
Could've been here for me.
My car was parked out front.

872
00:49:47.444 --> 00:49:49.405
Looks like they plan on coming back.

873
00:49:49.947 --> 00:49:51.824
I'm really gonna need a gun.

874
00:49:53.075 --> 00:49:57.121
<i>Hey...</i>

875
00:49:57.788 --> 00:49:59.707
<i>Call in the cavalry</i>

876
00:49:59.790 --> 00:50:03.961
<i>Hey...</i>

877
00:50:04.795 --> 00:50:07.131
<i>A taste of victory</i>

878
00:50:12.803 --> 00:50:17.183
<i>I'm gonna humor you
with the act of conversation</i>

879
00:50:19.518 --> 00:50:23.898
<i>I got my sunglasses on
from the sleep deprivation</i>

880
00:50:26.275 --> 00:50:28.068
<i>Should we drop you at home?</i>

881
00:50:28.152 --> 00:50:30.946
<i>Are you waiting
for a last dance?</i>

882
00:50:32.823 --> 00:50:35.743
<i>You know you never got
the call 'cause I didn't want</i>

883
00:50:35.826 --> 00:50:36.994
<i>The romance</i>

884
00:50:37.077 --> 00:50:41.290
<i>Hey...</i>

885
00:50:42.249 --> 00:50:44.084
<i>Call in the cavalry</i>

886
00:50:44.168 --> 00:50:48.172
<i>Hey...</i>

887
00:50:49.173 --> 00:50:51.717
<i>I'll take some victory</i>

888
00:51:11.403 --> 00:51:15.699
<i>Hey...</i>

889
00:51:16.367 --> 00:51:18.077
<i>Call in the cavalry</i>

890
00:51:18.160 --> 00:51:22.498
<i>Hey...</i>

891
00:51:23.374 --> 00:51:24.917
<i>A taste of victory</i>

892
